<subSubSection pageId="76" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="76.[151,1437,343,946]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,668,694]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Remarks</emphasis>
. This is a member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirby" authorityYear="1882" box="[612,784,667,693]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulphureipes">
<emphasis box="[612,784,667,693]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">P. sulphureipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (Shinohara, 1993). The maximum intraspecific 
<emphasis box="[1413,1427,668,693]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">p</emphasis>
- distance within 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara" authorityYear="1993" box="[331,652,703,729]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="sulphureipes" subSpecies="sulphureipes">
<emphasis box="[331,652,703,729]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">P. sulphureipes sulphureipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[723,791,704,730]" name="South Korea" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Korea</collectingCountry>
was 0.2% in COI (n=5) and 0.4% in NaK (n=4) and the nearest neighbour was 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kim" authorityYear="1963" box="[405,533,740,765]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coreanus">
<emphasis box="[405,533,740,765]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">P. coreanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, diverging by a minimum of 3.0% in the COI analysis and by a minimum of 0.9% in the NaK analysis.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="76.[151,1437,343,946]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
Without giving the source of information, 
<bibRefCitation author="Sundukov, Yu. N. &amp; Lelej, A. S." box="[670,957,811,838]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" pagination="62 - 119" refId="ref79983" refString="Sundukov, Yu. N. &amp; Lelej, A. S. (2012) Podotryad Symphyta - Sidyachebryukhie. In: Lelej, A. S. (Ed), Annotated Catalogue of the Insects of Russian Far East. Vol. I. Hymenoptera. Dalnauka, Vladivostok, pp. 62 - 119. [in Russian]" type="book chapter" year="2012">Sundukov &amp; Lelej (2012)</bibRefCitation>
simply noted “larvae on 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Shinohara" baseAuthorityYear="1993" box="[1237,1293,812,837]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Rosa" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1237,1293,812,837]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Rosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1307,1418,812,838]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
)” under the present subspecies. Most probably this is a lapsus. The closely related 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shinohara" authorityYear="1979" box="[1042,1176,847,873]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ishikawai">
<emphasis box="[1042,1176,847,873]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">P. ishikawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1243,1307,848,874]" name="Japan" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Japan</collectingCountry>
is associat- ed with 
<taxonomicName box="[239,369,883,910]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" genus="Astilbe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[239,317,883,909]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Astilbe</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[382,543,883,909]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Saxifragaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Saxifragaceae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Kameda, Y. &amp; Ibuki, S. &amp; Kiyoshi, T. &amp; Kakuda, T. &amp; Kojima, H." box="[564,816,883,909]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" pagination="167 - 178" refId="ref78036" refString="Shinohara, A., Kameda, Y., Ibuki, S., Kiyoshi, T., Kakuda, T. &amp; Kojima, H. (2016 a) Pamphilius ishikawai feeds on Astilbe: the first record of Pamphiliidae (Hymenoptera) associated with Saxifragaceae. Zootaxa, 4098 (1), 167 - 178. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4098.1.8" type="journal article" year="2016">
Shinohara 
<emphasis box="[685,740,883,909]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">et al.</emphasis>
2016a
</bibRefCitation>
) and these are more likely host plants of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara" authorityYear="1993" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="sulphureipes" subSpecies="sulphureipes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">P. sulphureipes sulphureipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
